headline: NikeSKIMS partnership, Wynn Resorts upgrade: Trending Stocks
summary: Brad Smith and Seana Smith take a closer look at the trending tickers of the trading session on today's episode of Wealth. Nike (NKE) shares are trading higher on news of a partnership with Kim Kardashian's Skims to create a new brand collaboration: NikeSKIMS. Wynn Resorts (WYNN) gains after Jefferies analysts upgraded the stock to a Buy rating with a $118 per share price target, citing growth related to the new Al Marjan location. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Wealth here. This post was written by Naomi Buchanan.

headline: Wynn Resorts Achieves the Most Forbes Travel Guide Five-Star Awards of Any Independent Hotel Company in the World
summary: Wynn Resorts has once again earned the most Forbes Travel Guide Five-Star Awards of any independent hotel company in the world. This year's recognitions reaffirm the Company's dedication to providing outstanding service, innovative design and exceptional experiences across its global portfolio of resorts.
